Mxolisi Mngadi, News24IPSS paramedics treating a woman who was mauled by her own Rotweiller. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A 67-year-old woman has been rushed to hospital after she was mauled by her own Rottweiler on Thursday morning, paramedics said.The woman was walking her dog at a park in Salt Rock near Ballito when the incident happened.She suffered extensive vascular injuries and muscular damage, said IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson Paul Herbst.She was first treated at the scene by IPSS medical advanced support paramedics before she was rushed to Ethekwini Hospital, Herbst said."She was rushed to a vascular surgeon as the extensive injuries she suffered had compromised her limbs due to blood flow," he said.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.